The paper deals with pattern matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of order-preserving matching and allowing for mismatches suggests that the paper may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM) categories. The algorithmic nature of the problem and the use of logarithmic time complexity suggest that the paper may also belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) or computational geometry (cs.CG) categories. Finally, the use of efficient algorithms and time complexity analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) category.
